FUNCTION
--------
1. Function is a self contained block of statement.
2. Every function performs some specific task.
3. Function is defined by function keyword followed by function name in traditional manner(changes or syntax may vary according to ES5 to ES6+ versions).
syntax: 
    function <function_name>(){

    }
4. We needs to provide body of a function to define it as a function.

Types of Function : 
-------------------
There are two types of function : 
a. Built-In function | In-Built function | Standard function | Library function | Predefined function : Whose definition part is already defined.
For ex : parseInt(), parseFloat(), Math.pow(), toPrecision() etc

b. UserDefined function : Whose definition part is defined by the programmer according to its programming needs.
For ex : 
    function add(){
        ......
    }

Advantages of function : 
------------------------
1. Function reduces program size.
2. Function increases code reusability.
3. Function reduces redundancy of code.
4. Function makes debugging easier.
5. We can create n number of functions.
6. A function can be called n number of times.

Category of Function : 
----------------------
1. No argument with no return type
2. No argument with return type
3. With argument no return type
4. With argument with return type

Basic syntax to use function in javascript
------------------------------------------

Javascript

function <function_name>(){
    ...
}

<function_name>();

Note : If we do not return any data or value from function then in that case by default return value of function will be undefined.